tasks.description:
Refactor `ToolCallCard.tsx` to extract the existing `ProgressOutput` component into a generalized `TruncatedOutput` component and apply it to the tool result `<pre>` block that currently renders untruncated.

## File: `apps/client/src/layers/features/chat/ui/ToolCallCard.tsx`

### Step 1: Rename the constant

Replace:
```typescript
/** Maximum bytes of progress output to show before truncation. */
const PROGRESS_TRUNCATE_BYTES = 5120;
```

With:
```typescript
/** Maximum characters to render before truncation (5KB). */
const TRUNCATE_THRESHOLD = 5120;
```

### Step 2: Replace ProgressOutput with TruncatedOutput

Replace the entire `ProgressOutput` function (lines 12-30) with a generalized `TruncatedOutput` component:

```typescript
interface TruncatedOutputProps {
  /** Text content to display, truncated if over threshold. */
  content: string;
  /** Maximum characters before truncation. Defaults to TRUNCATE_THRESHOLD. */
  threshold?: number;
  /** Additional className for the wrapper div. */
  className?: string;
}

/** Renders text content with character-based truncation and a one-way expand button. */
function TruncatedOutput({ content, threshold = TRUNCATE_THRESHOLD, className }: TruncatedOutputProps) {
  const [showFull, setShowFull] = useState(false);
  const isTruncated = content.length > threshold;
  const displayContent = isTruncated && !showFull ? content.slice(0, threshold) : content;

  return (
    <div className={cn('mt-2 border-t pt-2', className)}>
      <pre className="max-h-48 overflow-y-auto text-xs whitespace-pre-wrap">{displayContent}</pre>
      {isTruncated && !showFull && (
        <button
          onClick={() => setShowFull(true)}
          className="text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground mt-1 text-xs underline"
        >
          Show full output ({(content.length / 1024).toFixed(1)}KB)
        </button>
      )}
    </div>
  );
}
```

Note: `TruncatedOutput` is NOT exported — it is private to this file. The `cn` utility is already imported on line 5.

### Step 3: Replace the raw `<pre>` result block

Replace this block (lines 97-104):
```tsx
{toolCall.progressOutput && !toolCall.result && (
  <ProgressOutput content={toolCall.progressOutput} />
)}
{toolCall.result && (
  <pre className="mt-2 overflow-x-auto border-t pt-2 text-xs whitespace-pre-wrap">
    {toolCall.result}
  </pre>
)}
```

With:
```tsx
{toolCall.progressOutput && !toolCall.result && (
  <TruncatedOutput content={toolCall.progressOutput} />
)}
{toolCall.result && (
  <TruncatedOutput content={toolCall.result} />
)}
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] `PROGRESS_TRUNCATE_BYTES` is renamed to `TRUNCATE_THRESHOLD`
- [ ] `ProgressOutput` is renamed to `TruncatedOutput` with generalized props (`content`, optional `threshold`, optional `className`)
- [ ] The raw `<pre>` on the result block is replaced with `<TruncatedOutput content={toolCall.result} />`
- [ ] The progress output call uses `<TruncatedOutput>` instead of `<ProgressOutput>`
- [ ] Tool results under 5KB render fully with no button visible
- [ ] Tool results over 5KB show truncated content with a "Show full output (X.XKB)" button
- [ ] Clicking "Show full output" expands to full content (one-way, no collapse)
- [ ] Existing auto-expand behavior when progress arrives is unaffected
- [ ] Existing expand/collapse card behavior is unaffected
- [ ] No new dependencies are added

Create a new test file for the `ToolCallCard` component that validates the truncation behavior for both tool results and progress output.

## File: `apps/client/src/layers/features/chat/ui/__tests__/ToolCallCard.test.tsx`

This is a new test file. Use the jsdom vitest environment. The component under test is `ToolCallCard` from `../ToolCallCard`.

### Test Setup

```typescript
/**
 * @vitest-environment jsdom
 */
import { describe, it, expect, vi } from 'vitest';
import { render, screen } from '@testing-library/react';
import userEvent from '@testing-library/user-event';
import '@testing-library/jest-dom';
import { ToolCallCard } from '../ToolCallCard';
import type { ToolCallState } from '../../model/use-chat-session';
```

Helper to create a `ToolCallState` fixture:

```typescript
function makeToolCall(overrides: Partial<ToolCallState> = {}): ToolCallState {
  return {
    toolCallId: 'tc-1',
    toolName: 'Bash',
    status: 'complete',
    input: '{"command": "echo hello"}',
    result: null,
    progressOutput: null,
    ...overrides,
  };
}
```

### Test Cases

**Test 1: Short result renders fully (no button)**
```typescript
it('renders short result fully without a show-more button', () => {
  const shortResult = 'Hello world';
  render(<ToolCallCard toolCall={makeToolCall({ result: shortResult })} defaultExpanded />);

  expect(screen.getByText(shortResult)).toBeInTheDocument();
  expect(screen.queryByRole('button', { name: /show full output/i })).not.toBeInTheDocument();
});
```

**Test 2: Long result is truncated with show-more button**
```typescript
it('truncates result over 5KB and shows expand button', () => {
  const longResult = 'x'.repeat(6000);
  render(<ToolCallCard toolCall={makeToolCall({ result: longResult })} defaultExpanded />);

  // Content should be truncated to 5120 chars
  const pre = screen.getByText(/^x+$/);
  expect(pre.textContent!.length).toBe(5120);

  // Show-more button should be visible with size
  const button = screen.getByRole('button', { name: /show full output/i });
  expect(button).toBeInTheDocument();
  expect(button.textContent).toContain('5.9KB');
});
```

**Test 3: Clicking expand button shows full content**
```typescript
it('expands to full content when show-more button is clicked', async () => {
  const user = userEvent.setup();
  const longResult = 'x'.repeat(6000);
  render(<ToolCallCard toolCall={makeToolCall({ result: longResult })} defaultExpanded />);

  const button = screen.getByRole('button', { name: /show full output/i });
  await user.click(button);

  // Full content should now be visible
  const pre = screen.getByText(/^x+$/);
  expect(pre.textContent!.length).toBe(6000);

  // Button should be gone (one-way expand)
  expect(screen.queryByRole('button', { name: /show full output/i })).not.toBeInTheDocument();
});
```

**Test 4: Progress output over 5KB is truncated**
```typescript
it('truncates progress output over 5KB', () => {
  const longProgress = 'p'.repeat(6000);
  render(<ToolCallCard toolCall={makeToolCall({ progressOutput: longProgress, result: null, status: 'running' })} defaultExpanded />);

  const pre = screen.getByText(/^p+$/);
  expect(pre.textContent!.length).toBe(5120);
  expect(screen.getByRole('button', { name: /show full output/i })).toBeInTheDocument();
});
```

**Test 5: Short progress renders fully**
```typescript
it('renders short progress output fully without a show-more button', () => {
  const shortProgress = 'progress output';
  render(<ToolCallCard toolCall={makeToolCall({ progressOutput: shortProgress, result: null, status: 'running' })} defaultExpanded />);

  expect(screen.getByText(shortProgress)).toBeInTheDocument();
  expect(screen.queryByRole('button', { name: /show full output/i })).not.toBeInTheDocument();
});
```

Note: The `motion` library's `AnimatePresence` may need mocking if it interferes with rendering. If tests fail due to animation, add this mock at the top of the file:

```typescript
vi.mock('motion/react', () => ({
  motion: {
    div: ({ children, ...props }: any) => <div {...props}>{children}</div>,
  },
  AnimatePresence: ({ children }: any) => <>{children}</>,
}));
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Test file created at `apps/client/src/layers/features/chat/ui/__tests__/ToolCallCard.test.tsx`
- [ ] All 5 test cases pass: short result, long result truncated, expand button works, long progress truncated, short progress full
- [ ] Tests use `@testing-library/react` with userEvent for click interactions
- [ ] Tests validate content length, button presence/absence, and button text
- [ ] No arbitrary timeouts or `waitFor` without assertions
- [ ] `pnpm vitest run apps/client/src/layers/features/chat/ui/__tests__/ToolCallCard.test.tsx` passes

